The Springbok flanker suffered a grade two tear of his left medial collateral ligament whilst playing in Japan at the weekend. JOHANNESBURG - Jaco Kriel will play no part in the Springbok end of year tour after injuring his left knee.The Springbok flanker suffered a grade two tear of his left medial collateral ligament whilst playing in Japan at the weekend.Kriel has returned to Johannesburg to undergo treatment and is expected to be out for approximately four weeks. Flank Nizaam Carr and prop Lourens Adriaanse will stay on with the Bok side as replacements for Kriel and Jannie Du Plessis respectively.The tour kicks off with a match against the Barbarians on November 5th before playing England at Twickenham the following Saturday. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)